Kaitai Struct definition for parquet files. Apache Parquet is a columnar storage format. A Parquet file looks like:     [4B magic "PAR1"] [row groups & column chunks ...]     [FileMetaData (Thrift Compact Protocol)] [4B footer_len (LE u32)] [4B magic "PAR1"].   This Kaitai spec validates both magic markers, exposes footer offsets/lengths,   returns the raw footer bytes, and provides the middle payload as a raw slice.
